## Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React + Vite project.

### Changes Made:

**1. Package Installation:**
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 1.4.1 (latest)
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with resolved dependencies (172 new packages added)

**2. Analytics Integration:**
- Modified `src/App.jsx` to import and use the Analytics component
- Added `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'` at the top
- Placed `<Analytics />` component in all view returns to ensure tracking across the entire application:
  - Loading state
  - Authentication page (Auth)
  - Dashboard page
  - Pool view page
  - Comp form page (add/edit)

**3. Implementation Details:**
- Followed the official Vercel documentation for React/Vite projects
- Fetched latest instructions from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Used the React-specific import path: `@vercel/analytics/react`
- Wrapped each return statement with React Fragments (`<>...</>`) to accommodate multiple elements
- Maintained existing code structure and patterns

**4. Verification:**
- Build completed successfully (426.47 kB bundle size)
- No new linting errors introduced in App.jsx
- Existing linting errors in other files were not modified (unrelated to this change)
- No tests available to run (no test script configured)

### How It Works:
The Analytics component will automatically track page views and collect Web Vitals data when deployed to Vercel. The component is lightweight and non-blocking, ensuring it doesn't impact user experience.

### Next Steps:
After deploying to Vercel, analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab for this project.
